review_blob: Bottle 2014/15. Pours a hazy bloodorange color with a medium top. Aroma of dried hay, vinegar, apples and stables. Taste is sour and its fizzy on the palate. Hard to pick out anything except from the fact that this is an awesome beer. Medium-light body and high co2 levels.

Bottle from June 2014. Pours a dark brown with a medium tan head. Roasted malts on the nose along with chocolate, vanilla, cocoa and molasses. Taste is light sweet with a moderate frutyness. Some bready maltyness, a bit of whiskey and a long sweet finish.

Bottle. Pours clear brown, small offwhite top. Fruity aroma with notes of raisins and breaddough. Sweet caramelized malts. Taste is light sweet and malty. Toffee and caramel flavors along with a light bitter finish. Somewhat light bodied and avg+ co2

Bottle. Pours a dark brown looking black in the glass. A medium dense, creamy tan head. Aroma is quite fruity with a moderate roasty profile. Notes of caramel and chocolate. Some pine and resin as well. Taste is well balanced. Some sweetness at first is rounded off with a pleasant bitterness. Mellow roastyness bl3nds well with the chocolate notes. Finishes with a long coffee / chocolate flavor. Medium to full bodied with a slick mouthfeel. Avg co2.

Bottle. Pours a clear brown, coppery body with a medium light-tanned head. Moderate smokey aroma with some caramel and dried fruit. Taste is balanced, a slight bitterness. Notes of cured meat and somewhat complex maltyness. Clean and smokey. Medium-light body, avg co2.

2013 vintage. Pours a dark brown producing a large fluffy tan head. Aroma of dates and raisins. Sugary. Complex taste. Its light sweet, has a vinous touch with hints of red wine grapes and a long fruity finish. Abit warming as well. Full bodied and just above avg co2 levels.

Bottle. Pours a clear dark brown producing a medium tan head. Unsurprisingly there is a load of smokey aromas here. From smoked ham to burnt leather. Some lightly toasted malts as well. Taste has a rich malty flavor along with the abundance of smokey notes. Light sweet but supremely balanced. Finishes on a light bitter note and leaves a lasting smoked ham flavor.Medium body and co2 levels.

Bottle. Pours a dark brown with a medium tan head. Aroma is moderate roasty with notes of pine and resin. Some sweet malty notes along with caramel. Light bitter taste with a light to moderate roasty profile. Some coffee notes as well. Dry light bitter finish. Medium-light body with avg co2 levels.

Bottle. Pours a clear pale golden with a small white top. Aroma of citrus and grass. Pale malts and some resin. Crisp, light bitter taste with notes of citrus and pine. Dry, bitter finish. Light bodied with avg+ co2.

Bottle. Pours a clear brown with a medium offwhite top. Complex aroma with smoke, dates, wood and malts. Vinous fruityness. Light bitter flavor with smoke, cured meat and lightly roasted malts. Medium-full body. Finishes with a little warmth and a clean bitterness. Avg co2 levels.

Bottle. Pours a clear dark brown with a medium light tan head. Aroma of roasted malts and berries. Hints of leather and sea. Taste is light sweet, flavors of caramel, raspberries and roasted malts. Light bitter finish. Quite dry. Medium-light body and avg co2. Quite nice for a beer "crafted with a twist".

Bottle 3.1% Pours a clear golfen body with a small white top. Aroma of tropical fruits, pine and grass. Taste is light bitter with some fruityness. Highly drinkable this one. Light body with avg to soft co2. Lasting dry, light bitter finish.

Bottle. Unclear golden body with a small white top. Aroma of citrus, pine and some light caramel notes. Taste is quite mellow, light bitter with notes of citrus and grapefruit. Light bodied with avg co2 levels.

Tap at Beer Temple Amsterdam. Nice creamy white top. Light sour aroma with hints of hay and stables. Mellow, faint sour taste. Fairly neutral, not much bitterness. Faint fruityness. Fairly drinkable. Light body and avg to high co2 levels.

Bottle. Pours a hazy pale golden body with a nice white top. Smells of fresh grass and citrus. Loads of citrus. The flavor is bitter with more citrus. Its not too bitter, just about right. Crisp and drinkable. Medium bodied with avg+ co2.

Bottle. Pours a viscous black body producing a small tan head. Malts, roast and coffee on the nose. Hints of liquorice and chocolate as well. Taste is well balanced, light sweet, roasty and rounded off with a moderate bitterness. Lingering coffee flavors. Its full bodied with a thick texture and avg to soft carbonation. Quite nice.

Bottle. Slightly hazy, golden pour producing a medium white top. Looks great. Aromas of malts, resin and citrus. Notes of grapefruit and melon as well. Taste is light sweet at first with a hint of spicy warmth, then into a fruity and malty flavor. Finishes moderately bitter. Nice mouthfeel, slick, full bodied and with avg co2 levels.

Bottle. Pours a dark brown with a small tan head. Malty aromas with notes of wood, liquorice and dried fruits. Hints of smoke and caramel as well. Taste is light bitter with notes of dried fruit, whiskey and malts. Light toasted / roasty profile. Fairly balanced, albeit bitter. Finishes with a lingering bitterness as well. Medium bodied with soft to avg co2. Quite nice.
beer_name: Anchor Argonaut Collection: Anchor Barrel Ale

review_blob:
Bottle. Pours a clear golden body with a medium white top. Nice fruity aroma from the belgian yeasts, hints of citrus, candy and tropical fruits. 
Taste is very well balanced. Fruity, light sweet flavor with hints of honey and heather. Finishes on a slightly bitter note along with notes of pepper and a little bit of alcohol warmth as well. Fairly dry. Medium to full body with avg to high co2 levels. The belgians would approve I think :)
beer_name: Stone 20th Anniversary Encore Series: 08.08.08 Vertical Epic Ale

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a golden body with a medium white top. Aroma of citrus fruits, mango and melons. Taste is balanced, but tending towards bitter. Some citrus notes in the flavor as well, along with more fruity ones. Quite drinkable and nice. Medium body and avg co2 levels.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Beer Camp Tropical IPA

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a dark brown looking black in the glass. Medium tan head. On the nose there is a moderate malty-roasty profile with the addition of dark roasted coffee. Some alcohol, some liquorice and some earthen notes as well. Taste is light bitter with more roasted malts and coffee. Somewhat rounded and in balance with regards to sweet/bitter. Leaves a warming, roasty coffee finish. Full bodied with soft carbonation.

Bottle. Pours a clear brown with a small tan head. Complex aroma with oak, whiskey, cognac, candy and a whiff of alcohol. Dried fruits and light toasted malts. Taste is more fruity, raisins, dates. Sweet, caramel and toffee. And a touch of bitterness as well. This is tasty and potent! Long fruity, sweet and warming finish. Feels creamy, has avg to lively co2 levels.

Bottle. Pours a hazy pale yellow with a medium, frothy white top. Aroma is citrus and subtle fruity-esters. Fairly bitter taste, but its nice. Dry and highly drinkable this one. Some (citrus)fruity notes and all in all a good, but somewhat bitter saison. Light to medium-light body with avg to high co2 levels.
beer_name: S:t Eriks / De Molen Citra Saison

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a hazy pale golden with a large white top. Lovely, fresh aroma of citrus, lemonpeel, mango and resin. Taste is bitter with loads of citrusy, fruity notes. This is a really refreshing IPA! Highly drinkable. Body is medium-light with avg co2 levels.

Bottle. Pours a black body with a medium dense dark tanned head. Strong roasty aroma with intense espresso / dark roasted coffee beans. Taste is sweet but also with intense coffee flavor. Slightly one-dimentional, but I like coffeestouts so Im not complaining :) Velvety soft body with avg to soft co2 levels.

Bottle. Pours a viscous black body with a large dark tanned head. Aroma of smoke, roasted grains, spice and alcohol. The taste is somewhat sweet at first then into a mild to moderate chilli-burn. Well balanced finishes light bitter and with a mild burn from the chilli and some warmth from the alcohol. Full bodied with a slick mouthfeel. Co2 levels is soft.
beer_name: To l Smoke On the Porter - Fire in the Rye

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a jet black body with a dense, medium, dark-tanned head. Aroma of roasted grains, chocolate, liquorice, soy and hints of balsamico. Taste is well balanced. Some caramel-sweet maltyness, moderate bitterness from roasted grains and hops and some salty elements aswell. Finishes quite bitter with a lingering roasty, coffee flavor. The alcohol is well hidden. Nice imp stout this one. The body is full with a slick texture. Co2 level is avg.

Bottle. Pours a black body with a creamy, dark-tanned head. Looks good! Original aroma here. Not just roasty, but lightly spiced and with hints of coconut-liquor. Malibu anyone ? :) The flavor is abit messy, some spice, some coconut action, some roast and some alcohol. Light sweet but fairly balanced and finishing on a light bitter note. Body is full and it has a thick texture. The co2 level is soft to avg.
beer_name: West Coast Bryggeri / All In Brewing Handshake

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a dark brown looking black in the glass. A medium, dense dark tanned head. Looks nice. Aroma is moderate to light roasty, dried fruits and slightly vinous. Sweet. Taste is also sweet with some roasty elements. Notes of dates and raisins; leather and a hint of salt. Quite nice this one. Creamy on the palate with avg co2 levels. Long light bitter finish.

Bottle. Pours a black body with a medium dark tanned head. Sweet aroma with moderate roast, chocolate, caramel and a whiff of alcohol. Taste is fairly sweet but balanced. Chocolate, roasted grains, a hint of spice and a light bitter finish. A good imp stout. Full to medium-full body with soft to avg co2 levels.
beer_name: Samuel Adams Imperial Series Imperial Stout

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a clear pale golden body with a nice, creamy-looking white top. Lovely and intense citrus aromas with both lemonopeeland grapefruit. Taste is light fruity with more yeasty elements in addition to the citrus flavors. Fairly dry finish with some lingering bitterness. Quite refreshing and drinkable. Light to medium bodied with avg co2 levels.
beer_name: All In Brewing The Purpose of IPA - Grapefruit

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a viscous black body with a medium to large, dense, dark-tanned head. Malts and roasted grains dominate the aroma, there are notes of chocolate, coffee and hints of leather. Taste is also malt driven, moderate to high roasted flavor, coffee, well hidden alcohol and chocolate. Finishes quite bitter, leaving a lingering roasted / coffee flavor. The body is slick and its softly carbonated.

Bottle. Classy label! :) Pours a dark brown looking black in the glass. A medium creamy dark-tan colored head. Leaving nice lacings. Moderate roasty profile. Some salty elements, hints of chocolate and something earthy. Ive never had oysters so wouldnt know what to look for here.. :)
Taste is somewhat sweet with malts and molasses. Some spices are evident and i suppose this is the horopito. Its pretty mellow all in all even tho there is some alcohol warmth here as well. Creamy on the palate and softly carbonated. Full bodied. Good stuff. Original flavor profile with the spice additions.

Bottle. Pours a near black body with a creamy tan head. Looks good! Earthy aromas with malts and chocolate. Moderate roasty profile. Hints of liquorice. Taste is fairly roasty with notes of chocolate and malt. A fair bitterness to round it off. Nice mouthfeel despite the low abv. Avg co2 levels.

Can. Pours a dark brownish- near black body with a large, fluffy tan head. Aroma of malts and roasted grains. Hints of milk chocolate, vanilla and cocoa. Taste is sweet and malt driven. Moderate roasty profile and a mellow yet easily noticable chilli-heat. Pretty nice and fitting, not overpowering in any way. Hints of wood and smoke in the aftertaste. Medium to full bodied with avg co2 levels. I like it!
beer_name: Garage Project Day Of The Dead

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a black body with a big, dense, tan head. Looking good! Aroma is malty with light to moderate roast. Hints of liquorice, vanilla and chocolate. Some light fruityness too. Taste is sweet, but well balanced. Chocolate, malts and roast is dominating. And its damn good. Full bodied, oily on the palate and soft to avg co2 levels.
beer_name: Edge Brewing / Lervig Pure Decadence Imperial Stout

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a near black body with a fast dissipating, bubbly tan head. Complex aroma with raisins, sage, wood, liquorice and a whiff of alcohol. Taste is also complex. Loads of flavors here. Sweet caramel, toffee, liquorice, wood, rum and raisins. Vinous and slick on the palate. Medium to low levels of co2. Quite nice this one.

Bottle 2013. Pours a coppery body with hints of red and a medium, fully diminishing tan head. 
Aroma of bourbon, cherries and alcohol. Wood, candy and vanilla. 
Taste is more complex, the bourbon is there, but not too overpowering. Hints of cherries, vanilla and wood. Candy, dried fruits and notes of leather and liquorice as well. Pretty nice. The mouthfeel is slick and its medium to full bodied. Avg to high co2 levels, atleast for a barrel-aged.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Bourbon Barrel Quad

review_blob: Bottle. (bone dry mikkeller selection) Pours a clear golden with a bubbly white top. Strong aromas of hay, stables, vinegar, apples and wood. Taste is moderate sour with notes of citrus, vinegar and wood. Dry and refreshing! This is a really good geuze. Light to medium-light body with loads of fizz.

Bottle. Pours a coppery, brownish body with a frothy light tan top. Complex aroma with leather, honey, caramel, liquorice and a whiff of alcohol. Nice, rounded flavours with a mix of sweet malts and sour/salty liquorice notes. Notes of raisins and wood as well. Light bitterness. Fullbodied with high to medium high levels of co2.

Botlle. Pours a copper,bronze body with a large, dense light tanned head. Looks amazing. The nose is smokey! Loads of cured meat, leather and malts. Taste is also dominated by the smoked malts, but its not overpowering or "too-much" in any way. Well balanced, sweet at start light bitter finish. Body is medium to full with an avg co2 level. Really great stuff!

Tap. Clear pale with a small white top. Aroma is corn, metals and a light floral touch. Taste also has this metallic hint along with a light bitterness and some faint malts. Semi dry and bland. Classic industrial stuff..

Bottle. Pours a golden body with a nice medium white top. Good aroma; fruity, flowery with hints of citrus. Flavor is balanced, with loads of hop-flavors. Fruity and light malty. This is a nice and fairly complex pale ale.
Body is medium and the co2 levels are avg.

Bottle. Pours a clear pale golden with a small white top. Light floral aroma with citrus and pale malts. Taste is a bit harsh bitter with more floralness. Some malts but mostly the harsh bitterness, sadly.

Can. Pours a dark golden with a medium offwhite top. Aroma is malts and light fruity with hints of resin and pine. Taste is bitter, somewhat harsh actually. Some malty sweetness is there as well, but mostly bitter with hints of resin. Not quite convinced but its not bad. Medium body and co2.

Can. Pours a deep golden body with a small offwhite head.
Aroma is light malty with hints of metal, grapefruit and resin. Taste is fairly balanced. Light bitter, with some soapy thing going. Fair enough, but wont buy it again. Medium to light body, avg co2.

Bottle. Pours a golden body with a small white top. 
Aroma is nice with pine, citrus and resin. Clean taste with light citrus, moderate bitter and light malty. Quite drinkable. Light to medium body with avg co2 levels.

Bottle. Pours a brownish body with a medium, bubbly tan head. Nose is biiig bourbon, hints of liquorice, some leather and roasted malts. Taste is light sweet and light salty. Still loads of bourbon but not as dominating as the nose. Liquorice, leather and light roast. Body is lacking a little bit, but that is the usual price to be paid when barrel-aging. All in all pretty nice IF youre into bourbon. Soft co2.

Bottle. Pours a dark brown with a nice looking tan head. Light fruity aroma with a good dose of roasted malts and hints of leather. Taste is light sweet with a somewhat weird earthy flavor. Not too disturbing, but not too great either. The mouthfeel is medium and the co2 levels are soft to avg.

Bottle. Pours a near black body with a medium tan head. Malty aroma with a touch of fruitiness. Moderate to low roasty profile, hints of smoke and cured meat. Taste is also malty. Sweet but not overly. Hints of vanilla and a subtle roastyness. Quite nice actually. Not too heavy witch makes it quite drinkable. Medium body and avg to soft co2.
